node.text:
The fine folks at @lastdropbeerfestival featured our Dole Whip-inspired smoothie-style berliner in their festival last Saturday and shot some great footage in our new cellar space!

If you scored #TropicalHideaway cans out in their first shot at limited distribution today, give this clip a listen and make sure you’re storing those cans cold, drinking ‘em fresh, and giving them a proper tiki-shake before you open and pour! 

(Also, huge-huge-huge congrats to the Cast Members bringing #Disneyland back to life today! Come grab a draft beer at 20% off today [and everyday!] with your TWDC ID!)

🐢
🐢
🐢

#ATOMOGRAM 

We're NOW POURING the results of Eve's most critical maelstrom query -- #WillItBlend? 

This draft-exclusive variant was built on a 4BBL liquid pull of our Rum Barrel Aged #BrokenBlender Tiki Stout, then pushed through an absolutely irresponsible amount of coconut. It's dense and rich with an intensely buoyant, fluffy mouthfeel. It's only available here, while pours last.

node.text:
BOTTLE DROP: #BrokenBlender - Rum Barrel-Aged Imperial Tiki Stout • 12.54% ABV • Notes of orange zest and nutmeg garnish aromatic waves of dark rum and tropical fruit, setting the tone for this Painkiller cocktail-inspired imperial stout.

After eighteen months in Jamaican rum barrels, #BrokenBlender2021 was pushed through three unique rounds of 300lbs of fresh coconut. The full-bodied sweetness of a cumulative 900lbs of coconut was tempered with 400lbs of sliced pineapple pieces for a vibrant tropical tang, then finished with a twist of orange zest and a dash of nutmeg.
⁣⁣
Local-access bottles are now live on TOAST. Limit 4 per person. Orders must be retrieved on the day they're placed and are not available for proxy pick-up. Toast sales culminate at sell-through or at 10:00pm on Saturday 7/24; any remaining inventory will be sold in a proxy-friendly Eventbrite sale on 7/25.
⁣⁣
📱 • Order beer-to-go at the link in our profile!
🚗 • Pick up at #StageSelect from 12:00 - 10:00pm daily!⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

HELPFUL HINTS:

• Beers sold through our Toast platform (bottlelogic.com/orderonline) are limited to same-day, no-proxy pick-up at the brewery. We've used "locals only" language around Toast sales in the past -- to clarify, we mean that anyone visiting the brewery in person will be able to purchase and retrieve a same-day transaction. Toast sales give locals an early edge before inventory is opened to proxies in Eventbrite sales. 

• Beers sold through Eventbrite are open to proxy purchases and have a set two-week pick-up period. Proxy assignments can be adjusted through the link in your ticket confirmation email.

• Bottled beers are sold directly through Toast for about a week -- specific dates are always announced. Bottles remaining after the Toast sale become the Eventbrite sale inventory.

• First-run smoothie cans are always brewery-exclusive releases. Smoothie rereleases often, but not always, see limited distribution.

node.text:
WE'RE CLOSED TODAY! 

After sixteen months of pivot-filled pandemonium, we're closing up shop to celebrate the best team in the business with an epic "Christmas in July" party!

Bottle Logic is the collective heart and sweat and hope of the 40 people we're celebrating today. Their glowing passion and endless curiosity have been the foundation of our small business, and the enduring kindness they share with one another and with our community continues to light our path forward. 

We'll reopen tomorrow for business as usual from 12:00 - 10:00pm with @guacnrolltacos. 

You can always see our active schedule of beer releases, food truck vendors, and operational hours at the Events & Releases tab at bottlelogic.com!

node.text:
Fellow Innovators! It’s the proxy-friendly Eventbrite sale day for #DegreeOfMotion2021!

Fudgey chocolate and softly bitter chocolate wafer cookies zoom across the palate in #DegreeOfMotion, a Bourbon Barrel Aged Imperial Stout built to mimic the savory-sweet flavors of Oreo cookies. Medium-bodied with a bouncy marshmallow mouthfeel.

=============== SALE DETAILS ===============⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
• Tickets go live at the top link in our profile at 12:00pm, limit 6pp.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
• If you've already purchased bottles in our local-access direct sale, you're still welcome to participate in today's Eventbrite sale.⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
• Proxy pickup is welcome in our Eventbrite sales! ⁣⁣⁣⁣There is no limit on how many orders a person may retrieve as a proxy. Proxy registration takes place during the ticket registration, though you may edit details through the link in your confirmation email afterward.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
• You will need the following information to register a proxy: Their Full Name, Date of Birth, and email address.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣ Your proxy MUST show ID that matches these information fields to retrieve bottles.
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
=============== Pick Up Details =========⁣======⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
• Bottles are immediately available for retrieval at the brewery from 7/11 - 7/25. Please remember that we will be closed entirely on 7/13.
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣ ⁣
• Again, proxy pick-ups are permitted but must be registered through Eventbrite. You are able to adjust your proxy post-purchase through the link in your confirmation email. ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
• We strongly recommend picking up on weekdays from 6-10pm. Saturday/Sunday crowds are inevitable, avoid them as best you can! ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

"The scientific man does not aim at an immediate result. He does not expect that his advanced ideas will be readily taken up. His work is like that of the planter — for the future. His duty is to lay the foundation for those who are to come, and point the way. He lives and labors and hopes." - Nikola Tesla ⚡️ 

Pop a #StasisProject bottle and celebrate the 165th birthday of our brewery's Patron Scientist!

node.text:
People of Earth! The #DegreeOfMotion local-access sale is wrapping up tomorrow night at 10:00pm! 

#DegreeOfMotion is an Oreo-Inspired Bourbon Barrel Aged Imperial Stout, aged for just over a year and finished through a baby-brite tank filled with 300lbs of Jet-Puffed marshmallows, over one hundred gallons of marshmallow fluff, and 300lbs of Oreo wafers. Fudgey chocolate and soft bitterness from the chocolate wafer cookies alight from a bouncy, medium-bodied base of marshmallow sweetness and settle on the palate with a richness that increases as the beer warms.

Remaining bottles bounce over to the proxy-friendly Eventbrite sale this Sunday (7/11) at 12:00pm! (Top link in profile!)
